The women's 4x400m team, led off by Child, led from the very first leg to win in a new championship record of three minutes 27.56 seconds, finishing 0.22 ahead of Russia, with Czech Republic getting bronze.
Shortly afterwards the men's team of <Name>Michael Bingham</Name>, <Name>Richard Buck</Name>, <Name>Levine</Name>, who ran a superb third leg to put them in the lead, and <Name>Richard Strachan</Name> clocked 3:06.96 to finish more than half a second clear of Russia. They were initially disqualified because Buck came off the track but that was overturned when it emerged he had been knocked by a Polish rival.
